race.comment: PIPLUP (7) is a former Kent galloper who has had two runs for the new yard and another spell. Looks well placed this class and the trip suits fresh. Fitter for two hit-outs and expected to go close. TRINITY'S D'ORO (8) was a maiden winner five back then has been in the minors all four runs since. Races on speed and looks a leading hope again. MANCHEGO (1) ran on hard fresh to place over 1200m then just missed over 1350m latest. Fitter again and extra trip is a plus. This looks ideal now. DOUGAL MCKEEN (3) has been freshened since a near miss last time over 1430m at Traralgon. Can go one better. TRUE PROPHET (4) is much better than the last run and gets a chance to atone.
